result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler Ryan Janckila was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Must pay court costs and forfeiture within 6 months.
Must have no police contact that leads to an arrest and complete treatment program

records.addlTxt: 11:21 Defendant Tyler Ryan Janckila in court with attorney Christopher R. Bub.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin. THorie; guilty to Ct#1, dismiss Ct#2. No police contact within the last 6 months and complete treatment program and writes the Court, may apply for an expungement. pay fine of $465.60. Bub and Def agree.  Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def pleas guilty to Ct#1; Bub stipulates to a factual basis.  COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. Court finds and adjudicates Def guilty of Ct#1. Dismisses Ct#2. Thorie and Bub address sentencing. Def addresses the Court. Court: orders:  For expungement Def must have no police contact leading to an arrest, complete treatment program and pay the amount of $465.60 with in 6 months. (DNA surcharge and fine) Def must write a letter to the Court. Thorie: will file an amended complaint having just 1 count.   Appeal rights are given to the defendant.
Plea hearing on May 2, 2016 at 11:15 am.
